<br>
Any Vah Shir who has done their Sonic Bane weapons will likely want to push on with the Officer's cloak, and that needs raids on those earlier camps.<br>
<br>
Now, also consider this: how many people trigger the hollowshade war, forcing the Sonic Wolves to win so they can harvest substances, or the Owlbears for their perfect pelts and their own substances. <br>
<br>
The Vah Shir, to follow their racial quest, need to harvest a number of things from all three races in Hollowshade moor, so it is a real inconvenience to have others keep triggering the war there then leaving the area inhabited by Owlbears and Sonic Wolves only.<br>
<br>
So how then will Vah Shir who have struggled through Hollowshade Moore work feel if someone leaves Grimmling Forrest - which has been altered a great deal recently - in a similar state to that which Hollowshade moore is normally found in.<br>
<br>
I've been in Hollowshade five minutes after a reset to find 65th lvl characters killing off the Grimlings just so they can harvest the Owlbears and Sonic Wolves. Was a pain as I needed to get one item off the Grimlings before I could move on. I've visted that area for near a month solid before the war was fixed, finding only Owlbears and/or Sonic Wolves and no Grimlings. <br>
<br>
Only answer was to petition repeatedly, even suggesting the darn thing be put on a timer so the Vah Shir can actually have a chance at their quest work - or that the Vah Shir drops be moved to another zone such as the one side of shadeweavers that's rarely visited. Instead the War was turned back on. Now it's as bad as before for people triggering it, but at least there's a way of resetting the zone for a while.<br>
<br>
Now if I can get a group to gether to hit Grimmling, I'm not going to be too happy to find the earlier camps in Vah Shir hands (well, it's great in respect of IC and storyline, but not for Quest work), but that someone's not bothered finishing the job. So yes, getting it complete so the zone resets is something I'd do, so I can then get on with the quests I want to complete. It's nothing to do with upsetting you - or anyone else - who hadn't time to finish helping the Vah Shir dominate the zone, but rather that I can't wait in hope that someone is going to complete the cycle and that the zone's going to be in a state I can visit and do what I need to do the next time I log in. Basically - I'm in the same boat as yourself, just at the opposite end of it. And no - I've not been responsible for resetting the zone... yet...<br>
<br>
It's the problem with those kinds of zone - that some people need things from races that can be removed from the zone by kicking off a war or other sequence of events while others need or want things from the zone when only one race dominates the zone.<br>
<br>
There is an answer - get a group together to do all the work in one go. Just remember - different people need different things from zones like that, so if you leave the zone - or even if you're working on harvesting there, someone else may be working on getting the zone reset (legitimately - not by petition) so they can try and do their own quest work. Personally I ask when entering those zones, but not everyone will.<br>
<br>
